y for rheumatism.</unittitle><container id="aspace_4763d5d1c09767b4d45cc99b1c1c3f2d" label="Mixed Materials" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_7b535246e07a4f9cda662c8896a360c6" level="item"><did><unittitle>Note giving birth day of the three Silver Children (1857, 1861 [?], 1863).</unittitle><container id="aspace_898b1113740e47a2eba715d5ed5165a8" label="Mixed Materials" type="folder">1</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_46ed4ee338e0f9dacf8b5371cbc5734c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Treasurer's book of Local Assembly No. 406; 4 pp. only filled. (This organization was the local of the glass bottle workers' union, National Trade Assembly #143 of the Knights of Labor. Pertinent corres. and Xeroxes from selected pp. of <title>Proceedings</title> on file in this folder.)</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="approximate" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1890-02/1890-12" type="inclusive">Feb.-Dec. 1890</unitdate><container id="aspace_19487bc9d6b484a6cf2e8b324ff9ec3d" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_9e517de4515adbe6c384046fc27b2b0c" parent="aspace_19487bc9d6b484a6cf2e8b324ff9ec3d" type="volume">13</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_7087c471218345a79e54f5c970548c0b" level="item"><did><unittitle>Payment vouchers (61 items, Nos. 25-85) authorizing Silver, as treasurer of the organization, to pay stated sum to a certain person, in most cases, George P. Pierce.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1890-02-18/1891-07-07" type="inclusive">Feb. 18, 1890-July 7, 1891</unitdate><container id="aspace_ae4db4034b1f31c2a72ab28089f4ec90" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235834]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_dbac91ce9a3d3f280b4f86804c1c0ffe" parent="aspace_ae4db4034b1f31c2a72ab28089f4ec90" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_65c85852402f281e7a1e5316fb994282" level="item"><did><unittitle>4 loose sheets of calculati